\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {The headline scaling result (3-seed mean $\pm $ SD).} Pass-rate by strategy\nobreakspace  {}$\times $\nobreakspace  {}budget on 15 hard code tasks, Sonnet 4. S, L, and H are averaged over three independent on-policy runs; R was run once (extended-thinking variation across seeds is small at temp\nobreakspace  {}0) at the sweep's budget partition (a more generous partition lifts R to $86.7\%$; see footnote and \Cref  {tab:reasoning-baseline}). S's small dip from $B{=}1$K (80.0\%) to $B{=}5$K (77.8\%) is within the $\pm 3.1$\,pp seed noise on a 3-seed $\times $ 15-task suite; pass@$N$ is non-decreasing in $N$ in expectation but not pointwise across finite-sample on-policy seeds. \emph  {Reasoning-only and best-of-$N$ saturate well below 100\%}; all three iteration-with-feedback strategies reach $\geq 97.8\%$ at $B{=}20$K (L hit 100\% on 2 of 3 seeds; H on all 3; H is the only variant at strict 100\% across seeds). The architectural ordering across H, L is within seed noise on pass-rate; what separates them is token efficiency and reliability (\Cref  {sec:interaction}).\relax }}{12}{table.caption.37}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:scaling-curves}{{3}{12}{\textbf {The headline scaling result (3-seed mean $\pm $ SD).} Pass-rate by strategy~$\times $~budget on 15 hard code tasks, Sonnet 4. S, L, and H are averaged over three independent on-policy runs; R was run once (extended-thinking variation across seeds is small at temp~0) at the sweep's budget partition (a more generous partition lifts R to $86.7\%$; see footnote and \Cref {tab:reasoning-baseline}). S's small dip from $B{=}1$K (80.0\%) to $B{=}5$K (77.8\%) is within the $\pm 3.1$\,pp seed noise on a 3-seed $\times $ 15-task suite; pass@$N$ is non-decreasing in $N$ in expectation but not pointwise across finite-sample on-policy seeds. \emph {Reasoning-only and best-of-$N$ saturate well below 100\%}; all three iteration-with-feedback strategies reach $\geq 97.8\%$ at $B{=}20$K (L hit 100\% on 2 of 3 seeds; H on all 3; H is the only variant at strict 100\% across seeds). The architectural ordering across H, L is within seed noise on pass-rate; what separates them is token efficiency and reliability (\Cref {sec:interaction}).\relax }{table.caption.37}{}}
\newlabel{tab:scaling-curves@cref}{{[table][3][2147483647]3}{[1][12][]12}}
